32. Visual Identity System (Detailed Production Spec)
32.1. Visual pillars (must stay consistent across all features)
Prioritize readability under combat stress.
Maintain strong path identity in the shop and HUD.
Keep clear contrast between gameplay threats and player-owned effects.
Preserve clean silhouettes before adding detail density.

32.2. Core color token set (UI + card integration)
Maintain one stable palette file; do not hand-pick ad-hoc colors per screen.
Path tokens:
PATH_SUMMONER = #4CAF50
PATH_CRIT = #E53935
PATH_DEFENSE = #1E88E5
PATH_ECONOMY = #FDD835
PATH_PAINT = #8E24AA
PATH_HYBRID = #FB8C00
Neutral UI tokens:
UI_BG_DARK = #101418
UI_BG_PANEL = #1B232C
UI_TEXT_PRIMARY = #F2F5F7
UI_TEXT_SECONDARY = #A8B3BD
UI_WARNING = #FF7043
UI_POSITIVE = #66BB6A
Contrast requirement:
All text and icon overlays must meet a minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio at default UI scale.

32.3. Shop card visual anatomy (single standard)
Card render order:
Background panel -> rarity frame -> path outline -> icon -> title -> stat line -> cost block -> synergy hint.
Path outline thickness:
Base 2px, hover 3px, selected 4px.
Path strip indicator:
Use an 8px vertical strip on the left edge for instant path scanning.
Rarity markers:
Common: no corner gem.
Rare: one corner gem.
Epic: two corner gems.
Legendary: animated top notch with restrained glow.

32.4. Card state behavior
Default:
80% saturation, normal alpha.
Hover:
Scale 1.03, saturation +8%, glow alpha +15%.
Affordable:
Cost text = UI_POSITIVE and subtle pulse every 2.0s.
Unaffordable:
Cost text = UI_WARNING, card desaturates by 20%.
Purchased:
Quick confirm flash <= 120ms + soft sound cue; no long blocking animation.

32.5. Iconography rules
Assign one primary icon and one fallback icon to each path.
Icons must be recognizable at 20x20 and 32x32.
No icon should rely on color alone; shape identity is mandatory.
Line weight consistency target:
2px at 1080p baseline scale.

33. Combat Readability and VFX Budget Rules
33.1. Threat hierarchy visual priority
Priority 1 (enemy lethal telegraphs):
Use a bright edge, directional cue, and high-contrast ground marker.
Priority 2 (player damage procs):
Keep visible, but with shorter duration and lower brightness than enemy lethal telegraphs.
Priority 3 (ambient effects):
Keep low contrast and low motion; ambient effects must never compete with threats.

33.2. VFX intensity budgets (performance + clarity)
Max simultaneous major VFX bursts on screen: 8
Max alpha-overdraw heavy effects per frame: 12
Cap Summoner path unit trails at 50% opacity during swarm peaks.
Paint overlays must clamp saturation when tile density > 65% coverage.

33.3. Telegraph timing standards
Major enemy attack wind-up telegraph:
Minimum 650ms before hit confirmation.
Elite attack telegraph:
Minimum 500ms.
Boss one-shot pattern:
Minimum 900ms + unique audio cue.

33.4. Camera and screenshake policy
Screenshake must be optional and default to medium.
Boss slam max shake duration: 180ms.
Use micro-shake for rapid-hit effects with a cooldown (>= 300ms between shakes).
No camera shake for passive DoT ticks.

34. UX, Accessibility, and Clarity Suggestions
34.1. Information hierarchy in battle HUD
Top priority:
HP/shield, active cooldowns, summon cap usage, objective/wave timer.
Secondary:
Coins, combo counters, optional metrics (DPS panel toggle).
Tertiary:
Flavor/status detail logs in collapsible area.

34.2. Tooltip and language format standard
Line 1:
[PATH] [ROLE] one-sentence value statement.
Line 2:
Exact numeric effect at current level.
Line 3:
Upgrade preview delta for next level.
Line 4:
Synergy tags (2-4 max) with plain words.
Do not use vague terms such as "greatly increases" without numeric values.

34.3. Accessibility requirements
Colorblind presets:
Protanopia, deuteranopia, tritanopia profile toggles.
UI scale slider:
Minimum 85%, maximum 130%.
Combat text readability mode:
Bold font option + darker shadow stroke.
Input accessibility:
Support remapping for all core actions, with hold/toggle alternatives where practical.

34.4. Cognitive load management
Limit simultaneous tutorial popups to one.
Do not open blocking modal popups during active combat unless paused.
On the death screen, show one primary recommendation and no more than two secondary suggestions.

